❓ Deep Thinking Question

If I run:

terraform apply

Then manually delete the file.

Then run:

terraform apply

👉 What will happen?

Explain:

Step-by-step internal process

Why Terraform behaves that way

Which phase detects the issue

Solution:-
🔥 SCENARIO RECAP

terraform apply → file created ✅

You manually delete the file ❌

Run terraform apply again

✅ WHAT WILL HAPPEN?

👉 Terraform will recreate the file

🧠 STEP-BY-STEP INTERNAL PROCESS
Step 1: Terraform loads configuration

Reads .tf files

Sees:

“A file named hello.txt SHOULD exist”

Step 2: Terraform reads state file (terraform.tfstate)

State says:

{
  "resource": "local_file.example",
  "filename": "hello.txt"
}

👉 Terraform believes:

“File already exists”

Step 3: Refresh Phase (CRITICAL)

This is where your earlier understanding needed improvement.

👉 Terraform queries the real world via provider

In this case:

local provider checks filesystem

File is missing

Step 4: Drift Detection

Now Terraform compares:

Source	Status
Config (.tf)	File should exist
State (tfstate)	File exists
Real world	File missing ❌

👉 Mismatch detected → DRIFT

Step 5: Plan Generation

Terraform decides:

“Resource is missing → must recreate”

Plan output:

+ create local_file.example
Step 6: Apply Phase

Terraform calls provider

Recreates file

⚙️ WHY TERRAFORM BEHAVES THIS WAY

Because Terraform is:

Declarative + Desired State Engine

It does NOT care:

Who deleted the file

Why it was deleted

It ONLY cares:

“Does reality match my desired state?”

If not → fix it

🔍 WHICH PHASE DETECTS THE ISSUE?

👉 Refresh phase (before plan)

Important:

Happens during terraform plan and apply

Syncs real-world state with tfstate

⚠️ PRODUCTION INSIGHT (VERY IMPORTANT)

This behavior is:

✅ Good:

Self-healing infrastructure

Drift correction

❌ Dangerous:

If someone deletes:

Database ❌

Load balancer ❌

👉 Terraform will recreate it blindly

⚠️ This can cause:

Data loss

Downtime

Broken dependencies

🧠 SENIOR-LEVEL TAKEAWAY

Terraform is NOT intelligent.

It does NOT:

Ask for confirmation

Understand business impact

It ONLY:

Enforces declared state

🔥 INTERVIEW-LEVEL ANSWER (SHORT VERSION)

Terraform detects drift during the refresh phase by querying the real infrastructure through the provider. Since the file is missing but exists in state and config, Terraform plans to recreate it and applies the change to match the desired state.
